      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While the \"woke\" movement has undeniably advanced human rights for marginalized groups, labeling all criticism as \"reactionary\" ignores the legitimate concerns about unchecked censorship and the silencing of dissent. True progress isn't achieved by forcing a single moral narrative onto society, but by fostering a culture where accountability coexists with the freedom to challenge ideas without fear of retribution. Trying to stay in the middle is necessary because reducing complex social dynamics to a binary of \"good vs. evil\" often leads to the very polarization we are trying to solve.",
